roundHints.Hint 2: You get 1 cash for every layer of Bloon popped, plus some bonus at the end of each round.
roundHints.Hint 7: Keep playing Bloons TD 6 regularly and check for new updates - maps, heroes, challenges, and other awesomeness.
roundHints.Hint 12: The more you use a certain Monkey, the more upgrades you will unlock for using it.
roundHints.Hint 26: See those Zebra striped Bloons? They combine the meanness of White Bloons and Black Bloons, and contain one of each just for fun.
roundHints.Hint 32: You saw one Camo Bloon back on round 24. Hope you're ready for more!
roundHints.Hint 38: End of next round has 2 Regrow Rainbow Bloons. If handled poorly, 2 could turn into many more...
roundHints.Hint 39: First MOAB-Class Bloon next round. Don't say you weren't warned!
roundHints.Hint 41: Coming up: Regrow Rainbow Bloons and Camo Rainbow Bloons. You all sorted for this?
roundHints.Hint 45: Fortified Ceramic Bloons coming up next.
roundHints.Hint 50: Lots of Camo Ceramic Bloons could wreck your day. Just sayin'.
roundHints.Hint 54: BTD6 is awesome. Life is awesome too. Don't forget to have a break sometimes and do something else. Then play more BTD6!
roundHints.Hint 58: Can you pop Lead? Can you pop Camo? How about... Camo Lead?
roundHints.Hint 59: Final round for Medium difficulty coming next. Congratulations! If you can pop the BFB Bloon that is...
roundHints.Hint 62: If you played BTD5 you'll remember what Round 63 was like. If you are new to this game, let's just say: many tightly packed Ceramic Bloons.
roundHints.Hint 73: Next round: Camo Regrow Fortified Ceramic Bloons. Phew! What a mouthful.
roundHints.Hint 77: What happens when you cram 75 Ceramic Bloons into a tiny space? You're about to find out!
roundHints.Hint 79: Final round for Hard difficulty next. Throw everything you've got at the ZOMG Bloon. It's big and slow, but very very tough.
roundHints.Hint 89: What's a DDT Bloon you ask? Like a MOAB crossed with a Pink, Camo and Lead Bloon. In all the bad ways.
roundHints.Hint 100: Congratulations on beating round 100! Enjoy your reward!
roundHints.Alternate Hint 4: You know 'alternate' just means harder right?
roundHints.Alternate Hint 5: Did you panic when you saw the Camo?
roundHints.Alternate Hint 8: Hmm, wonder when the first Lead will appear?
roundHints.Alternate Hint 21: That's what we call a 'cash starve' round...
roundHints.Alternate Hint 39: Next round, MOAB as usual. Or is it?
roundHints.Alternate Hint 59: BFB next round. Or should that be FBFB?
roundHints.Alternate Hint 77: Next round is a real stinker...
roundHints.Alternate Hint 99: It wasn't that BAD was it?
roundHints.Alternate Hint 100: Congratulations on beating round 100! Enjoy your reward!
roundHints.Rogue Hint 1: Looks like lots of Bloons are headed this way! Popping them gives cash to purchase Towers, Boosts and Upgrades!
roundHints.Rogue Hint 4: Black and White Bloons! Black Bloons float right through explosions, White Bloons aren't affected by ice attacks!
roundHints.Rogue Hint 5: Camo Bloons... Not all Monkeys are gifted with the ability to see these Bloons.
roundHints.Rogue Hint 6: Purples and Leads! What pops one doesn't always pop the other, a true defense test.
roundHints.Rogue Hint 8: Fortified Lead Bloons! They sure look tough, even tougher than normal Lead Bloons.
roundHints.Rogue Hint 9: Two Ceramics. You'll need some good damage output to pop them.
roundHints.Rogue Hint 16: How strategic of those Lead Bloons to escort the MOAB
roundHints.Rogue Hint 22: 3 MOABs and a BFB walk onto the path. This isn't a joke.
roundHints.Rogue Hint 25: A round full of colorful Camo Bloons? What's the point of having so many colors if you can't see them.
roundHints.Rogue Hint 28: Rogue Legends is awesome. Life is awesome too. Don't forget to have a break sometimes and do something else. Then play more Rogue Legends!
roundHints.Rogue Hint 30: ZOMG! Surely there isn't anything larger!
roundHints.Rogue Hint 33: DDT's you say... Next round you say...
roundHints.Rogue Hint 45: What is that large purple thing in the distance?
roundHints.Rogue Hint 46: That is one BAD looking Bloon...

Door Gunner.description: Pick up a tower and allow it to shoot while mid-air.

Emergency Unlock.description: Unlocks locked Dartling Gunners and boosts their swivel speed for a short time.

Vine Rupture.description: Burst all track vines, doing big damage to all non-Lead Bloons. New vines will regrow after each Rupture.

Battle Cat Transform.description: Fully powered Battle Cat hits Bloons hard, also tearing away Camo property and Bloon immunities.

Link.description: Activate a tower's abilities as soon as they are ready.

Ambush Tech.description: Select an area. The Techbot will only activate if Bloons are inside.

Naval Tactics.description: Greatly increases attack speed of Brickell and nearby water-based Monkeys for a short time

Mega Mine.description: Deploys to any water area a devastating Mine that triggers on MOABs and stuns nearby Bloons

Blast Chain Ability.description: Sea mines fire off quicker for a short time

The Long Arm of Light.description: Greatly increases attack range and power for a short time & damages all Bloon Types

Blood Sacrifice.description: Sacrifice a targeted Tower to grant Adora large amounts of XP and boost her attack range and rate of fire for a short time

Ball of Light.description: Brings forth a powerful ball of energy to strike down the Bloons.

Transforming Tonic.description: Turns Alchemist into powerful attack Monster for 20 seconds.

Total Transforming Tonic.description: Transforms five Monkeys nearby into crazy attack monsters for 20 seconds.

IMF loan.description: Gives you $9,000 but you have to pay it back over time.

T Rex STOMP.description: Stuns up to ZOMG Bloons in a wide area.

Giga STOMP.description: STOMP hits the whole map and lasts longer.

Biohack.description: 4 closest Monkeys pop an extra layer per attack for 6 seconds. Affected Monkeys can't attack for 2 seconds after effect ends.

Bomb Blitz.description: When a Bloon escapes, a Bomb Storm will destroy every Bloon on the screen below a BFB.

Assassinate MOAB.description: Special missile flies out and does massive damage to MOAB class Bloons.

Moab Eliminator.description: Assassinate ability deals 6x damage with a short cooldown.

Turbo Charge.description: Makes this Monkey attack incredibly fast for 10 seconds.

Perma Charge.description: Makes this Monkey deal additional damage for 15 seconds.

Armor Piercing Shells.description: Shots can pop Black Bloons and do extra damage to Ceramic Bloons.

MOAB Barrage.description: Launches a barrage of shells at up to 10 MOAB-Class Bloons on screen, dealing massive damage each time.

Soul Harvest.description: Harvests a small number of Bloons near Corvus

Spirit Walk.description: Corvus can shift to any valid location

Dark Ritual.description: Harvests a huge number of Bloons near Corvus

RocketStorm.description: Launches a powerful storm of rockets in a wide cone.

RocketStormMAD.description: Each missile does extreme damage to MOAB-Class Bloons.

Super Monkey Fan Club.description: Converts up to 10 nearby Dart Monkeys including itself into Super Monkeys for 15 seconds.

Plasma Monkey Fan Club.description: Converts up to 20 nearby Dart Monkeys including itself into Plasma Monkeys for 15 seconds.

Jungle's Bounty.description: Generates cash and 1 life each use, plus extra cash per Banana Farm near the Druid

Overclock.description: Target another tower to supercharge its attack speed for a short time.

Ultraboost.description: Ultra-Overclocked Monkeys gain a small but permanent boost every time they are overclocked.

Drone Swarm.description: Etienne launches 4 more temporary drones to wreak some Bloon popping havoc

UCAV.description: High altitude surveillance drone becomes devastating combat drone for a short time.

Heartstopper.description: Allows Purple popping and prevents any regrow from happening for 10 seconds.

Sacrificial Totem.description: A totem that gives Camo detection, extra pierce, attack range, attack speed, and projectile speed to nearby Monkeys, especially Wizard Monkeys. Drains 10 lives.

MOAB Hex.description: Places a curse on a MOAB-class bloon, it takes damage every second until annihilated.

Glue Strike.description: Glues all Bloons on screen, causing them to take more damage from all sources while it lasts.

Glue Storm.description: Pelts the whole screen with glue for 20 seconds.

Cocktail of Fire.description: Hurls a flask of flammable liquid, burning Bloons that pass through the fire.

Firestorm.description: Sets the whole screen alight, burning all Bloons and granting the Heat It Up buff to all Monkeys.

Redeploy.description: Pick up and redeploy most Monkey types.

Special Poperations.description: Deploys a powerful special Monkey Marine with a machine gun.

Snowstorm.description: Freezes all regular Bloons on screen, briefly freezes White, Zebra, and Camo, and slows MOAB-class.

Absolute Zero.description: Ability is so cold it freezes all regular Bloons for longer, including White, Zebra, and Camo, slows MOAB-class longer, and greatly increases the attack speed of all Ice Monkeys for the duration.

MermonkyAbility.description: Launches a barrage of bouncing ice balls following target priority, or targeted point

MermonkyAbilityBig.description: Popseidon draws such power that a rogue wave floods the map with supercooled water, freezing all Bloons and reclaiming the weak for the sea

Ground Zero.description: Drops a huge bomb that destroys most things on screen.

Tsar Bomba.description: A very, very large bomb. Someone put a stop to this craziness!

Carpet Bomb.description: (Unofficial Description) Deploys 8 bombs in a designated path.

MOAB Takedown.description: Harpoons a MOAB class Bloon and brings it down.

ZOMG Takedown.description: Plunders extra cash from each MOAB-class Bloon taken down.

Large BAD Harpoon.description: (Unofficial Description) Harpoons the largest Bloon on screen including BADs, destroying it instantly.

First Strike Capability.description: A devastating missile strike targeting the largest Bloon on screen, plus splash damage.

Final Strike.description: (Unofficial Description) The Nautic Siege Core disables itself for 15 seconds before launching three massive nuclear missiles, leaving bloontonium pools

Call to Arms.description: Gives all Monkeys +50% attack speed and pops for a short time.

Homeland Defense.description: Ability now increases attack speed and pops by 100% for all Monkeys for 20 seconds.

Bombardment.description: Unleashes a rapid fire attack in a slightly wider area

Pop And Awe.description: Rains explosions over the whole screen, damaging Bloons and stunning them periodically

Sabotage.description: Lasts 15 seconds. During the sabotage, all Bloons move at half speed.

Grand Sabotage.description: Ability duration is longer and buffs Shinobi while active, and MOAB-Class Bloons spawn with less health during the sabotage.

Brambles.description: Creates a spiked bush on the track that can pop 50 Bloons. Lasts multiple rounds if not destroyed

Wall of Trees.description: Summons a wall of trees across the track that destroy all Bloons that enter. When full, the trees burst into money.

Rallying Roar.description: All nearby Monkeys can pop +1 layer for a short time.

Big Squeeze.description: Grabs a MOAB, BFB, DDT (if visible), or ZOMG and crushes it to bits over 5 seconds.

Psychic Blast.description: Psi unleashes a wave of power that stuns nearby Bloons for a long time.

Psionic Scream.description: Psi unleashes a silent scream that throws the Bloons into utter chaos.

Rapid Shot.description: Triple attack speed for a short time.

Storm of Arrows.description: Covers a large area in a deadly rain of arrows.

Scatter Missile.description: Rosalia's Workshop launches a missile that rains destruction from above.

Flight Boost.description: For a short time all nearby aircraft fly faster & Rosalia pursues Bloons over the whole map, using both weapons!

Kinetic Charge.description: Charge attaches to a Bloon, harnessing energy when the target takes damage. Then releases accumulated energy in a huge detonation.

Leaping Sword Attack.description: Sauda's dramatic Lead popping leap attack slams down on her targeted Bloons.

Sword Charge.description: Sauda slides along the whole track, devastating Bloons as she goes.

Retaliation.description: A lost life gives the Sniper 4x attack speed for a short time in retaliation.

Supply Drop.description: Drops a crate full of cash and will trigger Supply Drop for other Snipers if they're ready

Elite Supply Drop.description: Supply drop gives much more cash.

Spike Storm.description: Shoots out a thick layer of spikes over the entire track.

Concussive Shell.description: Shoots a guided shell to the largest Bloon on screen, stunning it.

Target Focus.description: For 15 seconds Mortar Monkeys target touch/cursor with increased accuracy

Artillery Command.description: Resets cooldown on all Bomb Shooters and Mortar Monkeys.

Darkshift.description: Shift to a valid location in range

ChampionDarkshift.description: Shift to a valid location anywhere on the map

Legend of the Night.description: When a bloon exits, spawn a portal that destroys all bloons that exit for a short time

Tech Terror.description: Destroys most Bloons completely and utterly within blast radius. Every third usage of the ability will deal +50% damage

The Anti-Bloon.description: Increased range, decreased cooldown, and does 5x damage

Blade Maelstrom.description: Covers the area in a storm of blades.

Super Maelstrom.description: Even more powerful Maelstrom ability that lasts longer.

Eruption.description: Temporarily increases projectile lifespan and adds a flame jet attack around the Crucible.

Meteor Impact.description: Targets a Bloon and strikes it with a meteor, dealing heavy damage in a large area around the target and spawns homing fireballs.

Summon Pheonix.description: Powerful phoenix wreaks Bloon havoc for 20 seconds.

Summon Lord Phoenix.description: Wizard Lord becomes a master of the flame, turning into a super powerful Lava Phoenix for a short time.

Arcane Metamorphosis.description: Magus Perfectus merges with the Phoenix and gains a powerful flame cascade attack for a short time.

Phoenix Rebirth.description: Consumes all mana to detonate the Phoenix making bloons in range take damage over time and spawn Zombie MOABs.

Spikeageddon.description: Fire a quick volley of exploding spikes over the entire map.

Take Aim.description: Target monkey gains improved range, accuracy, and Camo Detection.

Marked To Pop.description: Marks extra bloons, then proceed to attack all Marked Bloons

TakeAim2.description: Target monkey gains improved range, accuracy, and Camo Detection. Also increases attack speed.

Marked To Pop2.description: Marks extra bloons, then proceed to attack all Marked Bloons. Also increases attack speed.
